mes thomas burnett iii james o burnett iii james henry burnett jr thats the one james macon burnett jim burnett j macon burnett james macon burnett jr passed away in  mid s location birmingham al chelsea al relatives ann h burnett bonnie sue burnett brenda d burnett thats the one james l burnett james r burnett na location covina ca hacienda heights ca long beach ca fullerton ca whittier ca relatives cheryl anita burnett deontre m burnett james l burnett sr patricia e campbell michelle carbajal thats the one      advertising james mabry burnett  burnet bulletin eedition forms  submissions search form search home classifiedsplace a classified adcontacthighland lakes marketplacenewseducation and schoolsgovernmentengagements and weddingssportsbaseballbasketballfootballsoccersoftballtrack and fieldvolleyballother sportsobitspet obitscommentaryfeatureseventsmusiccalendarcoupons james mabry burnett submitted by bulletin on wed   am james mabry burnett september    may   james mabry burnett born september   passed away peacefully thursday may  surrounded by family james jim was born and raised in beaumont one of three children born to the late sam and eunice burnett james graduated from french high school in  he served in the u s coast guard for three years before meeting marie his wife of  years in  he settled in liberty hill with his family and became a small business owner he purchased the local laundromat and opened a convenience store the corner washateria and corner carry out became a well known landmark and gathering spot in downtown liberty hill always concerned about the youth in town he added an arcade and pool tables at the back of the store so they had a place to go he loved and encouraged not only his children but all of them james was involved in the community he volunteered for the fire departments in liberty hill and bertram he was the first to attend and complete fire training school he encouraged others to do the same he gave blood regularly earning recognition for giving more than  gallons through the years he volunteered his time recording books on tape at the library and served as a leader for scouting in round rock and liberty hill he loved to read loved old county music and dancing the most important thing to him was family james was a loving husband father uncle grandfather and friend he was fiercely loyal and protective of those he loved he touched many lives and will be remembered for his quick wit sense of humor love for words and infectious smile he was preceded in death by his parents his brother donathon burnett and sister wilma patrick he is survived by his wife marie burnett children larue williams and husband tommy rex burnett and wife carol phyllis burnett mark burnett and wife bjo and connie burnett sisterinlaw patricia burnett and brotherinlaw william patrick  grandchildren  great grandchildren two greatgreat grandchildren and many nieces and nephews a celebration of life was held saturday june  at cross tracks church a methodist community the family requests donations in lieu of flowers made to cross tracks church youth ministries arrangements under the care of edgar  jenkins family funeral home burnet rate this article  select ratinggive james mabry burnett give james mabry burnett give james mabry burnett give james mabry burnett give james mabry burnett  no votes yet log in to post comments search form search httpwwwwillyweathercomtxburnetcountyburnethtml jump back to navigation the burnet bulletin the burnet bulletin  s main st burnet tx      subscriber links eedition forms  submissions site links home classifieds contact highland lakes marketplace newseducation and schools government engagements and weddings sportsbaseball basketball football soccer softball track and field volleyball other sports obitspet obits commentary features eventsmusic calendar coupons follow us subscribe to our rss feed be a fan on facebook copyright   burnet bulletin burnet bulletin   south main  burnet tx    coupon